	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=209880><span id= >morromid</span></a><br><span id=notbold>15 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>After the last patch the whole zone seems to have more mobs running around. More Ice Burrowers and Mastodons for sure.<br><br>For Druids, as soon as you leave the tunnel coming into the zone from Sirens Grotto you will usually find that track will point you to some Brontotheriums and Mastodons that are stuck in the geometry right at the tunnel exit. You can't see them, but they are there. The druid &quot;Sense Animal&quot; spell is wonderful to find and target them.<br><br>I typically charm a bronto for a pet. Snare him, cast Glamour of Tunare, and then charm him. He has a lot of HP, I don't usually buf him. For me charm usually lasts quite a while. This zone is great for druid animal spells.<br><br>I then find a Mastodon and snare him. I used to root him but I finally figured out my little used repulse animal spell might be good and it was GREAT. Dot him, sick my pet on him and fear him. Just sit back and watch. Fights usually take a lot out of my pet and I usually had to heal but with Repulse Animal there is basically no damage. It's kind of funny to see two snared animals snailing across the snow. <br><br>Velium Hounds make fine pets too but they're faster and harder to snare. They break root more often. <br><br>I went 0 for 5 or 6 the other night in drops for Velium Mastodon Fur then the next night had two in a row and then 3 with nothing. Its quite variable but seems to be 1 in 5 I'd guess, or around that. <br><br>At the moment I have no problem selling Mastodon fur in the Bazaar. I still have the price at 1200pp and they all sell. There is only one other seller</p>&nbsp;<br>Morromid<br>61 druid<br>Terris-Thule</td></tr>
